Open SAP transaction “VL03N – Display Outbound Delivery” and search for the original order in the “External Deliveries with External Identification”. 
Insert order number and press “Enter
Double klick on the SAP order number that pops up and press Enter. 
Double check that the order contains the same items and quantity as the return order and copy the SAP order number. 
Open SAP transaction “VL09 – Cancel Goods Issue” and insert the SAP order number, press Execute
Tick the box for the return, press define date and put original order date. If prior to current month put the 1st of the current month. 
Press “Reverse”

Open “VL02N – Change Outbound Delivery” and insert the SAP order number. 
Press “Delete” if the complete order was returned.  
Add comment on updated order status in Stock Levels document and include the original removed SAP order number.  

If the order was partially returned, edit the order in VL02N to remove the returned parts using the edit mode to e.g.: 
Change quantity in an existing line 
Remove a line (minus button) 
Add a line (Plus button

After editing the order, repost it using the transaction “VL06O – Outbound Delivery Monitor”  
Re-post goods issue.  
